Partner connectors — fivetran, airbyte, and friends.

Partner connectors are third-party ingestion tools that databricks integrates with natively. They show up under partner connect in the workspace, the sign-up and billing flow through databricks, and they land tables directly into unity catalog.

When do you pick a partner over a managed connector? Three situations. When the source is in the long tail — something like marketo, stripe, or zendesk — where fivetran or airbyte has a connector and lakeflow connect doesn't yet. When you're already standardised on a partner tool across other warehouses and want one operational pattern. Or when you want a no-code interface for analysts to add new sources themselves.

The exam doesn't dig into specific partner tools. What it does expect is that you recognise lakeflow connect, partner connectors, and standard connectors as three peer options — and that you pick the managed connector when the source is supported.
